name: aki
description: Defined as Kidney Disease Improving Global Outcomes (KDIGO) stage >= 1, either due to an increase in serum creatinine or low urine output. 'True' if the patient develops AKI within the next 6 hours and 'False' otherwise.

name: stay_id
description: Unique identifier of the patient stay at an eICU unit of 208 hospitals in the US, collected between 2014 and 2015.

name: age
description: Age of the patient at hospital admission

name: sex
description: Gender of the patient. It takes one of the values {'Female', 'Male'}.

name: height
description: Body height of the patient at hospital admission

name: weight
description: Body weight of the patient at hospital admission

name: hr
description: Heart rate measured in beats per minute.

name: ph
description: pH of blood of the patient.
